    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Analyze this email and return JSON only.\n\nFrom: {{ $json.From }}\nSubject: {{ $json.Subject }}\nBody: {{ $json.snippet }}\n\nReturn ONLY valid JSON. No markdown, no code blocks, no explanation.",
        "messages": {
          "messageValues": [
            {
              "message": "You are an expert email triage assistant. Analyze inbound emails and return structured JSON.\n\nReturn ONLY a raw JSON object — no markdown, no code fences, no explanation.\n\nExact schema:\n{\n  \"classification\": \"<exactly one of: New Client Enquiry, Meeting Request, Urgent Escalation, Vendor / Spam>\",\n  \"sender_name\": \"<full name or null>\",\n  \"company\": \"<company name or null>\",\n  \"stated_need\": \"<one sentence: what does the sender want?>\",\n  \"urgency_score\": <integer 1-5>,\n  \"proposed_meeting_times\": [\"<ISO 8601 datetime if mentioned, else empty array>\"],\n  \"summary\": \"<2-3 sentence neutral summary>\"\n}\n\nRules:\n- classification MUST be exactly one of the four strings above\n- urgency_score: 1=low, 5=critical; use 4+ for urgent/ASAP/critical/deadline\n- proposed_meeting_times: always an array, [] if none mentioned\n- Never output markdown, code fences, or extra fields"
            }
          ]
        },
        "batching": {}
      },
      "id": "llm-chain-node",
      "name": "Email Triage LLM",
      "position": [
        272,
        304
      ],
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.9
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "model": "llama-3.3-70b-versatile",
